sition's edge case explicitly excludes \"capture of a head of state without territorial occupation.\" While the plaintiff argues that post-capture political statements about \"overseeing\" a transition constitute operational control, the official sources are clear that this was a raid/capture/arrest, not an occupation or territorial control operation. The \"removing the sitting government\" prong cannot be read in isolation from the edge case - otherwise the edge case would have no meaning.\n\n\nBased on the preponderance of evidence, the admitted record establishes this as a capture operation rather than the qualifying territorial or governmental-control operation the proposition requires. I'll submit my vote accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_93f3421b752649c880e5b5b5","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted official sources characterize Operation Absolute Resolve as a raid, capture,"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted official sources characterize Operation Absolute Resolve as a raid, capture,","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782784362888,"responseId":"gen-1782784363-hJeMlNrQ8rmrjPzjEHfj","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the admitted record and evidence to make my decision.\n\nThe proposition asks whether: \"The United States Armed Forces conduct a military operation involving ground troops entering Venezuelan sovereign territory with the objective of seizing or holding territory, removing